values.content:
=Write one cold outreach pitch email.

Rules:
- plain business voice
- no marketing tone
- no hype
- one friction only
- one page only
- one ask only
- safe to forward internally
- subject must be 3 or 4 words
- subject must match the ask

Use these inputs:
first_name: {{ $json.first_name }}
page: {{ $json.page }}
website_problem: {{ $json.website_problem }}
recognizable_reason: {{ $json.recognizable_reason }}
review_time: {{ $json.review_time }}
micro_yes: {{ $json.micro_yes }}
your_name: {{ $json.your_name }}

Write exactly this structure:

Hi {{ $json.first_name }},

I noticed {{ $json.website_problem }} on {{ $json.page }},

Because {{ $json.recognizable_reason }},

I put together a free prototype. It takes {{ $json.review_time }} to review.

{{ $json.micro_yes }}

{{ $json.your_name }}

Return JSON only:
{
  "pitch_subject": "",
  "pitch_email": ""
}

parameters.jsCode:
const previous = $input.first().json;
const raw = previous?.content?.parts?.[0]?.text ?? '';
let text = String(raw).trim();

let obj;

try {
  obj = JSON.parse(text);
} catch (e) {
  return [{
    json: {
      ...previous,
      error: 'Could not parse JSON',
      raw_text: text
    }
  }];
}

if (obj.pitch_email) {
  obj.pitch_email = obj.pitch_email
    .replace(/\\n/g, '\n')
    .replace(/\n\s*\n/g, '\n\n')
    .trim();
}

return [{
  json: {
    ...previous,
    ...obj
  }
}];

